# mu2e shifter & operations document sources
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# One entry per line. Lines starting with '#' are comments.
#
#   https://...        -> scraped as a normal web page
#   git-https://...    -> cloned & ingested as an MkDocs/Markdown git repo
#   sso-https://...    -> fetched via the Selenium SSO scraper (needs
#                         selenium_scraper.enabled: true + SSO creds)
#
# Replace the placeholders below with the real mu2e pages/repos.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- mu2e wiki / public web pages ------------------------------------------
# The mu2e wiki front page (known public landing page).
# Prefixed sso- so it goes through the Selenium (PassthroughSeleniumScraper)
# path — plain HTTP gets a 403 from Cloudflare's bot challenge.
sso-https://mu2ewiki.fnal.gov/wiki/Main_Page
# Add specific shifter / operations / run-plan pages, e.g.:
# https://mu2ewiki.fnal.gov/wiki/Shifts
# https://mu2ewiki.fnal.gov/wiki/Operations

# --- Git / MkDocs documentation repos --------------------------------------
# Prefix with git- . Example (replace with the real mu2e ops docs repo):
# git-https://github.com/Mu2e/your-ops-docs.git

# --- Fermilab SSO-protected pages ------------------------------------------
# Prefix with sso- . Requires selenium_scraper.enabled: true and SSO_USERNAME /
# SSO_PASSWORD in secrets.env. See configs/mu2e/README.md for the Fermilab SSO
# caveat. Example:
# sso-https://mu2e-docdb.fnal.gov/cgi-bin/sso/ShowDocument?docid=XXXX
